OL,3,CCaptain did 'absolutely nothing' to
OL,4,Cstop fatal tanker crash, jury told
OL,6,FMr Little said: "When a vessel is at
OL,7,Fan anchor there is a limited amount of
OL,8,Fmovement, but you can safely conclude
OL,9,Fin this case that it was, or should
OL,10,Fhave been, obvious to the defendant
OL,11,Ffrom the position on the radar of the
OL,12,FStena Immaculate that it must have
OL,13,Fbeen anchored."
OL,15,FMr Little said Mr Motin "manifestly
OL,16,Fbreached" his duty of care, adding:
OL,17,F"The risk of death, we say, was
OL,18,Fserious and obvious, and the
OL,19,Fnegligence and the level of the
OL,20,Fnegligence was so bad that it was
OL,21,Fgross."
