OL,3,CCaptain did 'absolutely nothing' to
OL,4,Cstop fatal tanker crash, jury told
OL,6,FThe judge Mr Justice Andrew Baker told
OL,7,Fjurors they must be "blind" to the
OL,8,Fnationalities of seafarers involved in
OL,9,Fthe collision between the two ships.
OL,11,FHe said: "This case is brought here,
OL,12,Fby which I mean, in this country,
OL,13,Fbecause this maritime collision
OL,14,Foccurred in English waters.
OL,16,F"It is not in any way unusual to find
OL,17,Fthat the sea farers involved came from
OL,18,Fa range of different nationalities."
